        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the TableMetadata schema — a Pydantic model for table-level metadata: unique identifier, page number, rotation angle, and title. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Table metadata model. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (standalone model). \par \b Output\/ \:  Pydantic BaseModel <computeroutput>TableMetadata</computeroutput> with page_id, uid, rotated_angle, title. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(7): pydantic.BaseModel] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>uid is always a non-empty unique string.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>rotated_angle is in degrees, may be 0.0 for non-rotated tables. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why include rotated_angle? A: OCR-based table recognition on scanned documents may detect tables at non-zero angles; this metadata preserves that information for correct rendering. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Initial creation with semantic markup] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 8[Table-level metadata — UID, page, rotation, title] =&gt; TableMetadata \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[TableMetadata]: TableDetector =&gt; AnnotateTableLocation =&gt; LinkTableToPage </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
